subsection.p:
  Requires Calculus. 
			Just as the case with instantaneous velocity, which was the derivative of the position, instantaneous acceleration is also a derivative - it is a derivative of the velocity as a function of time. In one-dimensional case of motion along the  x  axis, we define  a_x  by a derivative of  v_x .

				\text{Instanteous acceleration, } a_x = \dfrac{dv_x}{dt}
